<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2017-05-15</DATELINE><TITLE>The Multipurpose Tool of Social Media: Applications for Scientists, Science Communicators, and Educators</TITLE><BODY>Social media has become the fastest way to disseminate new information, share personal experiences, and discuss scientific reports in an open-access setting. It acts as an aggregator of news and reports, a platform for education, a means of public outreach, and a tool for scientific research. Each social media service offers unique communication benefits. This review discusses how scientists are using social media to inform and learn from social media communities, concentrating on microbiology and infectious disease.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>